  "identifier": "TRACLUS",
  "name": "TRACLUS: Trajectory Clustering Using Line Segments",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Implements the TRACLUS (TRAjectory CLUStering) algorithm by Lee, Han, and Whang (2007) <doi:10.1145/1247480.1247546>. The algorithm partitions trajectories into line segments using minimum description length (MDL), clusters segments via density-based spatial clustering (DBSCAN), and generates representative trajectories using a sweep-line algorithm. Supports euclidean, spherical (haversine), and equirectangular-projected distance calculations for geographic trajectory data.",
